  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Dietary intervention to prevent sarcopenia in elderly people. The objective of this study is
      to test whether combined nutrient intake plays an important role in stimulation of the muscle
      protein growth in elderly people; and whether it represent effective strategies to overcome
      the impaired muscle protein synthesis in elderly when compared with young subjects.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
